{"author":{"id":"a233f7149c353f9ab3ae23b55d153d65ff644d361cfb792a9f5fb047562f2604"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1731268090,"nonce":"GSLMwdoUKRMrTnG1fa2Qzj119+s=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOJl1IZM6dztvH","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/686","origin":"github"},"title":"Double clicking the window title should enter fullscreen","message":"**Describe the bug**\nIn macOS, double click a window title will usually maximize the window.\nWhen you click the window title with Aerospace running, it flickers the screen:\n- macOS resizes the window to span the whole area of the display\n- Aerospace resizes it back to it's original size\n\nI would expect to see the window enter fullscreen, than could then be toggled off via command or by double clicking the window again.\n\nAs a workaround, I configured my BetterTouchTool to execute the relevant aerospace command when the window title is double clicked. It still flickers, but it does the expected behavior.\n\n**Related issues you could find**\nPlease make sure to search for duplicates.\nIf you couldn't find the duplicates, linking related issues is helpful anyway.","files":null}]}